  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Hypothesis: When performed under ultrasound guidance, there is improvement in the sensory and
      motor blockade obtained with stimulating popliteal catheters versus those placed without
      nerve stimulation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
